text.tspan: Sex ratio at birth vs. at five years old, 2015
Sex ratio at birth, measured as the number of male births per 100 female births versus the sex ratio at five years old,
measured as the number of males per 100 females. The grey line represents the point of equal ratio: countries which
lie above this line had a higher sex ratio at birth than at five years old.
Sex ratio at five years old
Source: UN Population Division (via World Bank), OWID based on UN World Population Prospects (2017)
